      "id": "PopularPost67709",
      "post_content": "Right, so for those who don't know how to make this card work well, I'll point out the obvious. This works well with sacrifice outlets. Be it the Devour mechanic, doubling up on [Innocent Blood](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Innocent Blood) or [Barter in Blood](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Barter in Blood), or mucking about with tokens and a [Vampire Aristocrat](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vampire Aristocrat), you'll be able to wipe out almost all opposing creatures. It destroys regardless of regeneration, shroud, or indestructability. It works wonders in multiplayer, and as an enchantment, only white and green have good answers to the destruction. It doesn't even need to be built around- though when it is, generally via a sacrifice deck- the destruction is truly greater than one would expect. And at four mana, the only downside is that is requires heavy black commitment. But that's the colour that will be getting the most use out of it anyway.\n  \n   \nFor further details, see the comments on more recent printings. Those fine ladies and gentlemen should have more specific... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "DoctorKenneth",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost67709\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">Right, so for those who don't know how to make this card work well, I'll point out the obvious. This works well with sacrifice outlets. Be it the Devour mechanic, doubling up on <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Innocent Blood\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Innocent Blood\">Innocent Blood</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Barter in Blood\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Barter in Blood\">Barter in Blood</a>, or mucking about with tokens and a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Vampire Aristocrat\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vampire Aristocrat\">Vampire Aristocrat</a>, you'll be able to wipe out almost all opposing creatures. It destroys regardless of regeneration, shroud, or indestructability. It works wonders in multiplayer, and as an enchantment, only white and green have good answers to the destruction. It doesn't even need to be built around- though when it is, generally via a sacrifice deck- the destruction is truly greater than one would expect. And at four mana, the only downside is that is requires heavy black commitment. But that's the colour that will be getting the most use out of it anyway.\r<br/> <br/>For further details, see the comments on more recent printings. Those fine ladies and gentlemen should have more specific... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 67709)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" 