      "id": "PopularPost74479",
      "post_content": "(Card Rating: **4.0**) Grave Pact is always a pleasure to play in a multiplayer format. If your oponent's do not have an answer for an enchantment in thier hand, any strategy they have involving even the most ***sturdy*** of creatures (i.e. [Progenitus](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Progenitus)) will be fruitless. In light of the hefty 3 **black** mana required to cast it, Grave Pact is a rather difficult card to splash. Because having more than one in your hand equates to a dead card, Grave Pact makes my list of **superb** \"one of's\". Since you will be already running black, I recommend [Demonic Tutor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Demonic Tutor) and [Vampiric Tutor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vampiric Tutor) to make it *seem* like you are running three in your deck. If you are on a budget, [Diabolic Tutor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Diabolic Tutor) will suffice. In my favorite casual **black**/**red** goblin deck, I run 1 Grave Pact along with... 4 [Mogg War Marshal](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mogg War Marshal), 2 [Goblin Chirurgeon](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Goblin Chirurgeon), 2 autoca... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Misago",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost74479\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">(Card Rating: <b><u>4.0</u></b>) Grave Pact is always a pleasure to play in a multiplayer format. If your oponent's do not have an answer for an enchantment in thier hand, any strategy they have involving even the most <b><i>sturdy</i></b> of creatures (i.e. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Progenitus\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Progenitus\">Progenitus</a>) will be fruitless. In light of the hefty 3 <u><b>black</b></u> mana required to cast it, Grave Pact is a rather difficult card to splash. Because having more than one in your hand equates to a dead card, Grave Pact makes my list of <b>superb</b> \"one of's\". Since you will be already running black, I recommend <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Demonic Tutor\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Demonic Tutor\">Demonic Tutor</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Vampiric Tutor\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vampiric Tutor\">Vampiric Tutor</a> to make it <i>seem</i> like you are running three in your deck. If you are on a budget, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Diabolic Tutor\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Diabolic Tutor\">Diabolic Tutor</a> will suffice. In my favorite casual <b>black</b>/<b>red</b> goblin deck, I run 1 Grave Pact along with... 4 <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mogg War Marshal\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mogg War Marshal\">Mogg War Marshal</a>, 2 <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Goblin Chirurgeon\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Goblin Chirurgeon\">Goblin Chirurgeon</a>, 2 autoca... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 74479)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_po